            "content": "; Comprehensive coverage for --average with periodic options.\n;\n; Tests interactions between --average (-A) and periodic grouping flags\n; (--monthly, --weekly, --quarterly, --yearly) for both balance and\n; register reports, with single accounts, multiple accounts, --collapse,\n; and late-appearing accounts.\n;\n; Related issues: #1087 (balance count inflation), #1950 (per-account\n; register averages), #2980 (collapse + distributed expenses regression).\n\n; --- Journal data ---\n\n2024/01/15 Groceries\n    Expenses:Food    $100\n    Assets:Bank\n\n2024/01/20 Bills\n    Expenses:Rent    $1000\n    Assets:Bank\n\n2024/02/15 Groceries\n    Expenses:Food    $200\n    Assets:Bank\n\n2024/02/20 Bills\n    Expenses:Rent    $1000\n    Assets:Bank\n\n2024/03/15 Groceries\n    Expenses:Food    $300\n    Assets:Bank\n\n2024/03/20 Bills\n    Expenses:Rent    $1000\n    Assets:Bank\n\n; --- Test 1: Balance --monthly --average, single account ---\n; Average of $100, $200, $300 = $200\n\ntest -M -A bal Expenses:Food\n                $200  Expenses:Food\nend test\n\n; --- Test 2: Balance --monthly --average, parent with children ---\n; Food: $300/2 posts-per-child... no, count = 3 visited posts, total $600, avg $200\n; Rent: 3 visited posts, total $3000, avg $1000\n; Expenses: 6 visited posts, total $3600, avg $600\n\ntest -M -A bal Expenses\n                $600  Expenses\n                $200    Food\n               $1000    Rent\n--------------------\n                $600\nend test\n\n; --- Test 3: Register --monthly --average, per-account independence ---\n; Each account maintains its own running average independently.\n; Food: $100/1=$100, $300/2=$150, $600/3=$200\n; Rent: $1000/1=$1000, $2000/2=$1000, $3000/3=$1000\n\ntest -M -A reg Expenses\n24-Jan-01 - 24-Jan-31           Expenses:Food                  $100         $100\n                                Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\n24-Feb-01 - 24-Feb-29           Expenses:Food                  $200         $150\n                                Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\n24-Mar-01 - 24-Mar-31           Expenses:Food                  $300         $200\n                                Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\nend test\n\n; --- Test 4: Register --monthly --average --collapse ---\n; Collapsed totals: $1100, $1200, $1300\n; Running average: $1100/1=$1100, $2300/2=$1150, $3600/3=$1200\n\ntest -M -A --collapse reg Expenses\n24-Jan-01 - 24-Jan-31           <Total>                       $1100        $1100\n24-Feb-01 - 24-Feb-29           <Total>                       $1200        $1150\n24-Mar-01 - 24-Mar-31           <Total>                       $1300        $1200\nend test\n\n; --- Test 5: Register --yearly --average ---\n; All data is in one year, so just one period.\n\ntest -Y -A reg Expenses\n24-Jan-01 - 24-Dec-31           Expenses:Food                  $600         $600\n                                Expenses:Rent                 $3000        $3000\nend test\n\n; --- Test 6: Register --monthly --average, account appearing late ---\n; Rent appears in all 3 months, Food only in months 2 and 3.\n; When Food first appears in month 2, its per-account average should be\n; independent: $200/2 = $100 (not inheriting Rent's running total).\n\ntest -M -A reg Expenses:Rent\n24-Jan-01 - 24-Jan-31           Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\n24-Feb-01 - 24-Feb-29           Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\n24-Mar-01 - 24-Mar-31           Expenses:Rent                 $1000        $1000\nend test\n",
